By Onyebuchi Ezigbo A total of 1,204 newly confirmed cases of Covid-19 were reported in the country on Monday. The daily report of newly confirmed cases of Covid-19 infections posted by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on its website said that 1,204 new confirmed cases and seven deaths were recorded in Nigeria. The report said that till date, 91,351 cases have been confirmed, while 75,699 cases have been discharged and 1,318 deaths recorded in 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). The 1,204 new cases were reported from 21 states â€” Lagos (654), FCT (200), Plateau (60), Kaduna (54), Kano (40), Rivers (30), Edo (28), Nasarawa (25), Kebbi (19), Bauchi (18), Oyo (13), Akwa Ibom (12), Bayelsa (11), Ogun (11), Delta (9), Abia (8), Benue (5), Imo (3), Borno (2), Sokoto (1) and Osun (1).